episode_title: 711 - The One With All The Cheesecakes

content.description: Chandler and Monica’s, Chandler is sitting at the kitchen table eating cheesecake. The box it came in is also on the table.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Ohh. Mmm.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi.
content.parenthetical: Comes in the front door and walks towards the kitchen.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Hey, you have got to try this cheesecake.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, y’know I’m not that much of a sweet tooth. I—(Chandler puts a forkful of the cheesecake in her mouth.)—Wow. My God, so creamy. Oh my God, this is the best cheesecake I have ever had. Where did you get this? (She reaches over to look at the label on the box.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: It was at the front door. When I got home. Somebody sent it to us.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Chandler, this is not addressed to you. This is addressed to Mrs. Braverman downstairs. (Gasping) Thief.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I—no! I didn’t read the box before I opened it. And you can’t return a box after you’ve opened the box.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Why, why not?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Because it’s too delicious.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Chandler, you stole this cheesecake. That is wrong.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: No-no-no! It is going to be okay, because Mrs. Braverman is gonna send away for a free one and that way we all win! The only losers are the big cheesecake conglomerate, (Reading the label) Momma’s Little Bakery. (Pause) I feel terrible, I’m a horrible, horrible, horrible person.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, I’m sorry, what?

content.description: Central Perk, everyone except Rachel is there as Joey gets up and starts putting on his coat.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: All right, I should get going, big day at work. Y’know I’m in a coma? Today, they do this test on me and it turns out I’m not brain dead.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: So…

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ah-ah-ah Mr. Smartie Pants, it’s just my character that’s not brain dead. Hey, so Pheebs, we still on for tonight?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Absolutely!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I’ll see you at 8:00.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Okay. (Joey exits.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh, what’s at 8:00?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, I have dinner plans with Joey. We get together about once a month to discuss the rest of you guys.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Wow, did not know that! May I say how lovely you look today?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Duly noted.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Thanks. (Phoebe gets up to get a refill.) (To Monica) Oh! So for tomorrow, do you want to rent a car and drive down together or what?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What are you talking about?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Cousin Frannie’s wedding, it’s tomorrow night.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: You were invited?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: No.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: My God, I can’t believe this! I mean I knew that mom and dad were invited, but I thought that was it! I mean from the ages 7 to 9 Frannie and I were inseparable!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well, maybe since the age of 9, Frannie’s made some new friends.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well l-look okay, it’s probably just a mistake. Let me call Aunt Sheryl okay? Maybe you are invited and the invitation just got lost in the mail.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Yeah, well you call her and tell her that y’know when we were kids her precious little Frannie tried to undress me several times, okay? And if I hadn’t have stopped her, there probably wouldn’t even be a wedding to go to.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Y’know, she tried to undress me too.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I used to undress my cousin Glenn. (Monica looks at him then shushes him.)

content.description: [Scene: Joey and Rachel’s, Monica, Chandler, Rachel, and Ross are playing Monopoly as Phoebe enters angrily.]

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Joseph Francis Tribbiani are you home yet?!!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Umm, I think he’s still out. What’s wrong?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, I’ll tell you Rachel Karen Green, I had plans with Joey tonight and he left me this note. (Hands it to Rachel.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: “Pheebs, can’t make it, got a date. Talk to you later. Big Daddy.” (Laughs) Big Daddy?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh that’s a nickname we were trying out.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey, y’know what nickname never caught on? The Ross-A-Tron! (Monica shakes her head in disgust.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh! Here’s Joseph Francis!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh-Wha-Ho! What are you middle naming me for?! I left you a note!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: So what?! That doesn’t give you the right to ditch me!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey, you can cancel plans with friends if there is the possibility for sex!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Phoebe he’s right, that is the rule.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: I don’t accept this rule. When we make plans, I expect you to show up. Okay, I can’t just be a way to kill time ‘til you meet someone better! Y’know boyfriends and girlfriends come and go, but this (Motions that their friendship) is for life!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Wow! I’m so sorry; I had no idea it would bother you this much.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, it does.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Okay, can I-can I make it up to you? Huh? I’m sorry. (They hug.) How about uh, dinner tomorrow night?! I’ll pay for myself!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Okay, you wore me down.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey Joe, while you’re over there how about another beer for the Ross-A-Tron?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: The Ross—Is that back?!! (Chandler motions no.)

content.description: Monica and Chandler’s, Rachel enters to find Chandler staring at another cheesecake box.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Another cheesecake came! They delivered it to the wrong address again!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: So just bring it back downstairs, what’s the problem?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I can’t seem to say goodbye.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Are you serious?! Chandler, we ate an entire cheesecake two days ago and you want more?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well I’ve forgotten what it tastes like okay?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: It was cheesecake. It was fine. It had a buttery, crumbly, graham cracker crust, with a very rich yet light, cream cheese filling… (Pause) Wow! My whole mouth just filled with saliva!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Y’know what? Forget it! We are just hungry! We have not had lunch! We are just light-headed! So let us go out and have lunch and forget about the cheesecake.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Yeah and we’ll drop it off downstairs so that we’re not tempted.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Good idea. Where do you want to go to lunch?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Momma’s Little Bakery, Chicago, Illinois. (They exit with the cheesecake.)

content.description: Central Perk, Monica and Joey are there. Joey is reading a newspaper.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Awww! Mel Torme died.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Joey, that paper’s like a year old!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Aw! Does that mean the Sam Goody’s sale is over?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Hey.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: So I finally heard back from Aunt Sheryl and apparently it wasn’t a mistake. Ahh, there’s-there’s limited seating in the hall.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Limited seating?! (Screechingly) I am just one tiny person!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well yeah, but she doesn’t know that. I mean, the last time she saw you-you would’ve turned one of those little wedding chairs into kindling.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Limited seating! Oh, that is such a lame excuse! That’s not the reason she’s not inviting me!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh what’s the big deal?! I wasn’t even invited to the ceremony, just the reception. And-and y’know what? If it makes you feel any better, Joan and I will just make an appearance and then, and then we’ll-we’ll leave early as a sign of protest.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Joan?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yeah, Joan Tedeski my date. She’s an assistant professor in the Linguistics department. Tall, very beautiful, and despite what some people say, not broad backed!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Wait a minute, you got Ross Geller and guest?! I wasn’t invited and you got “and guest?!”

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Uh-uh, excuse me, I do have to interrupt on Ross’s behalf. I-I think the rule applies here y’know, since she has a chance to get on broad back…

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Not broad backed!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Wait a minute, y’know, you’re bringing me!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? I can’t cancel on Joan!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Why not?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Bec—Did you not hear me?! She’s an assistant professor in the Linguistics department, okay? They’re wild! Why do you want to come anyway?

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Because! She’s my cousin. I mean, we grew up together! We’re family y’know? Well that’s important to me.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Okay, all right, I’ll take you. I’ll go call Joan. (Does so.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Aww that’s nice. Family should be there, huh? This is her wedding, happiest day of her life.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: We’ll see.

content.description: The Lobby of Chandler and Rachel’s building, Chandler and Rachel are returning from lunch.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well, thank you for lunch.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What? Wait a minute, I didn’t pay, I thought you paid!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: So apparently we just don’t pay for food anymore. (Rachel laughs then Chandler notices something.) Do you see what I see?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Its still there! (The cheesecake they returned to Mrs. Braverman is still lying in front of her door.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Mrs. Braverman must be out. (They move closer to it.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: She could be out of town. Maybe she’ll be gone for months.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: By then, the cheesecake may have gone bad. We don’t want her to come back to bad cheesecake.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: No that could kill her.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well, we don’t want that.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: No, so we’re protecting her.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: But we should take it.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: But we should move quick.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Why?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Because I think I just heard her moving around in there.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! (Rachel grabs the cheesecake and they take off upstairs.)

content.description: Central Perk, Monica and Phoebe are entering. As Phoebe is sitting down, she recognizes someone sitting at the counter.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: (whispering) Oh my God! That’s David!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: David who?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: David the scientist guy, David that I was in love with, David who went to Russia and broke my heart David!

content.speaker: David
content.text: Oh my God!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, you say someone’s name enough, they turn around.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Phoebe?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: David! (He kisses her cheek) What-what are you doing here? Aren’t you supposed to be in Russia?

content.speaker: David
content.text: Yeah, I’m just, I’m just in town for a conference. Umm, God you look phenomenal!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well… Yeah. You look great too. Did you get a haircut?

content.speaker: David
content.text: Yeah. Well I-I got like thirty of them.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Umm, look I-I-I got a confession to make…

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Uh-huh.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Uh, I-I-I was hoping to run into you here. I didn’t know whether I should call or not, y’know I-I was only in town for a few days. And y’know, I didn’t want to intrude on your life or-or anything like that, but I-I really wanted to see you and—but I didn’t know if you wanted to see me.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, of course I would want to see you. I…I think about you all the time.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Really? Because I think about you all the time.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Really?

content.speaker: David
content.text: I mean, there’s a statue in Minsk…

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Uh-huh.

content.speaker: David
content.text: That reminds me of you so much, I mean umm, it-it’s actually of Lenin. But, y’know at certain angles…

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Umm, anyway…Do you want to have dinner tonight?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yes! Oh no!

content.speaker: David
content.text: Oh. Uh, what?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: I can’t. I can’t believe I have plans, I can’t. Can you do it tomorrow night though?

content.speaker: David
content.text: Uh no, I have to go in a few hours. I have to be on the red-eye. Well listen, y’know, next time you’re in Minsk umm…

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Phoebe, can I talk to you for a second?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Uh-huh. (They go over and talk.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: What are you doing?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well, I have plans with Joey tonight.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: So! He’ll understand!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No he won’t. And that’s not even the point! Monica, I made a whole speech about you do not cancel plans with friends! And now y’know what? Just because, potentially, the love of my life comes back from Russia just for one night, I-I should change my beliefs?! I should change beliefs! No! No! No, if I don’t have my principles, I don’t have anything!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: God, you are so strong.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Or! I should rush through dinner with Joey and I can meet David at 9:00!

content.description: Joey and Rachel’s, Rachel and Chandler are eating the cheesecake right out of the box.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh my God! That is so good!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I’m full, and yet I know if I stop eating this, I’ll regret it.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What do you got there?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh it’s umm, it’s tofu cake. Do you want some? (He makes a disgusted noise and heads for his room, Chandler follows him in.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What are you doing tonight?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Huh? Uh… (He starts taking off his pants.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Dude! Dude! (Motions that Joey should pull up his pants.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh! (Pulls up his pants.) Sorry. Uh, I’ve got those plans with Phoebe, why?

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh really? Uh, Monica said she had a date at 9:00.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What?! Tonight?!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: That’s what Monica said.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: After she gave me that big speech?! She goes and makes a date with a guy on the same night she has plans with me? I think she’s trying to pull a fast one on Big Daddy!

content.description: Cousin Frannie’s Wedding Reception, Monica and Ross are entering and finding their table.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh here, I think this is us. (Reading the name cards.) Yeah.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Limited seating my ass. Let’s see who made the cut. (To the couple sitting to her right.) Hi!

content.speaker: The Wedding Guest
content.text: Hi!

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: I’m Monica Geller. Who do you know the bride and groom?

content.speaker: The Wedding Guest
content.text: Oh, I used to work with Frannie.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Used to work with her. Used to! I’m a relative and I didn’t get invited! A blood relative! Blood!!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Stop saying, “Blood” to strangers.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: So, how about you huh? How do you know the happy couple?
content.parenthetical: to the couple on her left

content.speaker: The Second Guest
content.text: We went to college with both of them and now we live next door.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Okay, you’re fine.

content.description: [Scene: Iridium Restaurant, Phoebe and Joey are looking at the menus as the waiter comes to take their order.]

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: Are you guys ready?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yes! I will have the green salad, umm the house salad, and water’s fine.

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Okay.

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: And for you sir?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yeah, this slow roasted salmon, just how slow are we talkin’ here?

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: It’s uh, it’s already been roasted.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Ohh, then no. Maybe I should hear those specials again.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh Joey, we’ve heard the specials three times! Okay? There’s prime rib, mahi mahi, and a very special lobster ravioli. (She grabs his menu and hands it to the waiter.)

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: Actually we’re out of the lobster ravioli. (Putting Joey’s menu under his arm.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Oh well, that changes everything! (Grabs his menu and starts looking at it again. The waiter leaves.) Y’know what Pheebs?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Huh?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: You were right before. I mean, friends are so important.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah, I’m very wise. I know.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Y’know-y’know what I really want?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: What?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Is to have a long, long talk. Y’know? Get Joey out on the open road and really open him up.

content.speaker: The Waiter
content.text: Any progress?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Yes! I will have the lobster ravioli.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: God Joey, this is taking forever!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What’s the rush? What?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: W-w—I just—it’s that—I have—y’know I have-I have an appointment. And it’s very important.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Whoa-whoa, what is it?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well… It’s a date.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: A date?! No, no Pheebs you-you must be mistaken, because I know you wouldn’t schedule a date on the same night you have plans with a friend!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Come on Joey, don’t make me feel badly about this.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No, I’m gonna!! That’s right! Yeah, you made me feel really guilty about goin’ out with that girl! Like-like-like I did something terrible to you! And now Pheebs, you’re doing the same thing!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: That—It’s not the same thing! This is totally different! This is with David! Remember David, the scientist guy? Okay, he’s very special to me.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Okay, well my girl from the other night was special. She was a scientist too!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: She was?

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Well, she graduated from high school!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Okay, whatever. Y’know what? I don’t have time to convince you because he’s only here for four hours, and I’m gonna go see him! (Gets up and leaves.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Fine!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah!

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Fine!

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Yeah! (She exits.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: What are you still doin’ here?! I told you, lobster ravioli!

content.description: Outside Central Perk, Phoebe is running up to meet David.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Hey!

content.speaker: David
content.text: Hey! Oh, I was just about to leave. I-I-I-I didn’t think you were coming.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, I wouldn’t miss this.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Well, I’m very glad you’re here. (Kisses her hand.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh, you’re such a gentleman. (Grabs his arm.) Come on! We’re going to my place! (Drags him off to her place.)

content.description: Joey and Rachel’s, Rachel is eating the cheesecake and Chandler enters and catches her in the act.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Are you eating the cheesecake without me?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Mm-mmm. (Nods no.)

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: I will give you a hundred dollars to whistle right now. (She tries to whistle and blows little chunks of cheesecake out of her mouth.) How can you eat the cheesecake without me?!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh, what are you going to do?! Are you gonna go run tell Monica?! Are you gonna tell Joey?! No! Because then you will have to tell them what we did! We are dessert stealers! We are living outside the law!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Y’know what? I don’t trust you with this cake anymore! And I got it first, and I’m takin’ it back! (Grabs the cheesecake and heads for his apartment.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What?! What?!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh yes!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Wait a minute!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh yes!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh no-no-no-no-no, no you don’t!
[Cut to Chandler and Monica’s as they enter.]

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh yes! Oh yes!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: You think I trust you with it?! No! We’re gonna split it! You take half and I take half!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Well that’s not fair, you’ve already had some!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: What? Oh, well then y’know what? I think Monica would be very interested to know that you called her cheesecake dry and mealy.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: What do we use to split it?

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay! (Grabs a knife and cuts it in half.) All right, pick a half.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Okay well, this side looks bigger. Uh… There’s more crust on this side. Y’know? So, maybe if I measured…

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh for God sake just pick a piece!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: All right, I’ll pick that one. (Points.)

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: That’s also the smaller piece. (Puts the piece onto a plate.) Okay, there you go. Enjoy your half my friend, but that is it. No sharing. No switching, and don’t come crying to me if you eat your piece too fast. (As she’s saying that she is backing out the door, when she finishes she turns around to return to her place, stumbles and drops the cheesecake on the floor.) Oh!!!!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Ohhh!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Okay, you gotta give me some of your piece.

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Oh-ho-ho-ho-no! No! No switching! No sharing, and don’t come crying to me! Ha-ha-ha! I may just sit here and have my cake all day! Just sit here in the hallway and eat my… (Rachel knocks the plate from his hand and it falls on the floor. That process leaves just the forkful Chandler has, Rachel starts to go after that little bit and Chandler retreats into his apartment.)

content.description: Cousin Frannie’s Wedding Reception, Monica and Ross are sitting at the table, alone, as a woman approaches.

content.speaker: The Woman
content.text: Ross, sweetheart!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Oh, hey Aunt Millie.

content.speaker: Aunt Millie
content.text: Isn’t it a beautiful wedding?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Yes, yes it is. It’s uh… (Aunt Millie uses this opportunity to grab Ross and kiss him on the lips. After she leaves Ross quickly wipes his mouth with a napkin.) Every time on the lips! Why?! Why on lips?!
(Cousin Frannie and her husband enter.)

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Here’s Frannie. Hmm, won’t she be happy to see me? (Starts to get up and greet Frannie.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Now wait a minute, you be nice! All right? I didn’t bring you here so you can ambush her.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Frannie was the one who found your Playboys and showed them to mom.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: That bitch! (He gets up and they go over to ambush Frannie. Monica taps on Frannie’s shoulder.)

content.speaker: Frannie
content.text: Monica! What…

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Am I doing here? Why? Surprised to see me? Ross brought me. How do you like that?!

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Hi Frannie, congratulations.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: You invite my brother, you invite my whole family, and not me?! Why?! What—Why wouldn’t you want me at your wedding? What could I have possibly done?! (Frannie’s husband walks up.) Stuart!

content.speaker: Frannie
content.text: I believe you know my husband.
(Monica is shocked into silence.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: So it’s really a question of who could you have possibly done.

content.description: Outside Central Perk, David has a cab waiting to take him to the airport and he’s saying goodbye to Phoebe.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Oh, I hate this but I-I-I have to go. I-I can’t miss my flight.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Are you sure? I’ll bet there’s another flight to Minsk in like…

content.speaker: David
content.text: July. Umm, (He speaks Russian.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: That’s really beautiful. What does it mean?

content.speaker: David
content.text: Please, clean my beakers. I don’t get out of the lab much.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: That’s good. I got to admit, I thought it was something else.

content.speaker: David
content.text: Yeah, I… Well I really actually wanted to say umm, that, but um, I figured I probably shouldn’t because y’know, I…have to leave.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: You’re right! You’re right. Don’t say it.

content.speaker: David
content.text: I-I do though.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: I do too. (They kiss.)

content.speaker: David
content.text: Bye Phoebe. (He gets in and the cab drives off. Joey walks up and witnesses that event.)

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Okay, now’s not the time Joey. All right? You can yell at me tomorrow.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: No! No! No Pheebs, I’m not gonna yell at you. I just y’know, started thinking about you and David and I…remember how bummed you were the first time he left. And I just… Oh Pheebs, come here. (He hugs her.) Are you okay?

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: No I’m not okay. The only guy I’ve ever been crazy about has gone to Minsk and I may never…I may never see him again. (Crying.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Hey, y’know you could always visit him.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Oh right, like they’re gonna let me have a passport.

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: Anything I can do? Whatever you need.

content.speaker: Phoebe
content.text: Well—But—Now, if-if you can achieve positronic distillation of sub-atomic particles y’know before he does, then he can come back. (They hug again.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: I can give it a shot.

content.description: The Hallway, Chandler and Rachel are on their knees with forks trying to salvage what they can of the cheesecake off of the floor.

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Oh! Yay! Look! There’s a piece that doesn’t have floor on it!

content.speaker: Chandler
content.text: Stick to your side!

content.speaker: Rachel
content.text: Hey, come on now!
(Joey finishes climbing the stairs and sees them. Chandler and Rachel both stop and look up at him. Joey sits down on the step.)

content.speaker: Joey
content.text: All right, what are we havin’? (Starts digging in.)

content.description: Cousin Frannie’s Wedding Reception, Ross and Monica are at the door and about to leave.

content.speaker: Monica
content.text: Oh wait I forgot my wrap.

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: What? Oh, okay. Wait here. (Goes to get it, but before he gets there Aunt Millie sits down on it forcing him to pull it out from behind her which gets her attention.)

content.speaker: Aunt Millie
content.text: Hi sweetie! Are you leaving?

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Well…

content.speaker: Aunt Millie
content.text: Give us a kiss. Come on! Come on!
(Ross hesitates then leans down trying to get her to kiss his cheek, but she moves his head around and kisses him on the lips again.)

content.speaker: Ross
content.text: Why?! Why on the lips?! (He wipes his mouth on Monica’s wrap and walks off, leaving Aunt Millie stunned.)
